critter.name: Coelacanth
critter.desc: The coelacanth is a deep-sea fish that has been around since the age of the dinosaurs. They were long thought extinct, so when living specimens were discovered, it was quite a shock! Now I'll just have to figure out where in the museum to display it- fish or fossils!
critter.quote: Blast from the past! I caught a coelacanth! Think positive! Be a coela-CAN!
